<doc id="1042665" wikidata="Q6449726" url="?curid=1042665" title="Kvichak Bay">
<text>Kvichak Bay is an arm on the northeast side of Bristol Bay in southern Alaska, at . It is long and wide. The Kvichak River flows into the bay at its furthest northeast point, while the Naknek River comes in from the east about to the south of the Kvichak.

