<doc id="1042707" wikidata="Q30898679" url="?curid=1042707" title="Game Pak">
<text>Game Pak is the brand name for ROM cartridges designed by Nintendo for some of their earlier video game systems. The &quot;Game Pak&quot; moniker was officially used only in North America, Europe, Oceania, and South Korea. In Japan, Nintendo uses the term when referring to Famicom, Super Famicom and Nintendo 64 game paks, and for the Game Boy line and Virtual Boy.

They include:
* Nintendo Entertainment System Game Pak
* Super Nintendo Entertainment System Game Pak
* Game Boy Game Pak
* Nintendo 64 Game Pak

